# Security (Always Active)

## Secrets

- **NEVER** hardcode secrets (API keys, tokens, passwords) in source code
- Store secrets in `.env` files (gitignored) and access via environment variables
- Use secret management services in production (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)

## Input Validation

- Validate all external input at system boundaries
- Use parameterized queries — never string-format SQL
- Sanitize user input before rendering in HTML/templates

## Authentication & Authorization

<!-- ADAPT: Include project-specific auth patterns -->
- Never trust client-provided identity claims without server-side verification
- Use established auth libraries — do not implement custom crypto

## OWASP Top 10

<!-- OPTIONAL: Include if compliance targets include OWASP -->
Automated validation via `scripts/validate-owasp-alignment.sh`:
- A01: Broken Access Control — no hardcoded role bypasses, no CORS wildcards
- A02: Cryptographic Failures — no MD5/SHA1, no hardcoded keys
- A03: Injection — no SQL injection, no command injection, no XSS
- A07: Auth Failures — no hardcoded passwords
- A09: Logging Failures — no silent exception handling

## Dependencies

- Pin dependency versions (no wildcards in production)
- Run dependency audits regularly (`scripts/validate-dependencies.sh`)
- Keep dependencies updated to patch known vulnerabilities
